criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  left colon and rectal lesions matching the criteria of ESD removal: depressed/flat
             elevated morphology and irregular or nongranular surface pattern, larger than 20 mm;
             lesions that cannot be optimally and radically removed with standard polypectomy or
             EMR

          -  age ≥18 years

          -  ability to sign the informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  deep submucosal invasion diagnosed by distorted pit (Kudo's type V) and/or capillary
             (Sano's type III) patterns [5];

          -  poor general condition (American Society of Anesthesiologists score ≥ 3);

          -  coagulation disorders;

          -  pregnancy and breastfeeding;

          -  inability to sign the informed consent.
